The epic lozenge isn't escaped properly in the issue sidebar (when I click an issue in planning view):

!http://monosnap.com/image/GWaAeeH5jZ0AlpXEqtpkKdiZX.png!

h3. Steps to reproduce

# Create a new scrum board;
# Create a new sprint;
# Add the gadget "Days Remaining in Sprint" in your dashboard;
# Configure it with your board and your sprint just created;
# Save it;
# Browse to the scrum board and under the "cog" icon (Tools) click in "Configure";
# Browse to the "Working Days" tab;
# Check all the 7 days of the week;
#- If you check the gadget now, it will appear a wrong random number as the number of days remaining;
# Now uncheck any day (leaving only 6 days) checked;
#- If you check the gadget now, you will see the correct number of days remaining;

- *If you keep decreasing the number of days checked everything will work just fine. This only happens with the 7 days checked.*

- *The "non-working days" will also generate random erroneous numbers in the gadget if the 7 days of the week are checked. If you have less than 7 days checked, the "non-working days" will be counted just fine in the gadget*.

- *This also seems to affect the Burndown chart (and consequently its gadget) as per the screenshot attached.*

+Current behaviour:+
1. create a parent task with more than one sub-tasks;
2. move some of the sub-tasks to the Done column;
3. click _Release_.

Sub-tasks are included in the released version, and so it appears as if a task was "partly released". That's not always valid, and so users should be asked if they intend to release sub-tasks without their parents (similarly to when they're asked if parent should be updated once all sub-tasks have been finished).

