On the Agile boards, when an issue is clicked and its details are shown in a window that opens on right of the browser window, there is no way to change the size of the issue details windows. This was possible in GreenHopper 3.x. From ticket GHS-2295 it show that the iframe has cut off due to numbers of limitations with the iframe. 

However, in GreenHopper 6.2.1, the issue details view dialog is very thin and small, there are some users are complaining about it. 

It will be great if we can add a resize button in a future release of GreenHopper

Current text:
{quote}Days and time zone defined below will be used for reporting in the Burndown Chart{quote}

Suggested text:
{quote}The days and time zone defined below will be used for reporting in the Burndown Chart, Control Chart and Version Report.{quote}

